I have visited this place many times but after my last time visiting I must leave this review. As an awareness for everyone.  On the last weekend prior to COVID taking over, 2nd week of March 2020, I decided to go visit this place to celebrate my 30th birthday with a large group of friends ; about 20 people. It was a great night and with day light savings happening, we lost an hour. During that night, we had a large bill; there were many bottles purchased. The police then crashed the place around 2:00AM , leaving us with one hour lost. I had just purchased 3 additional bottles.  When Police came, I told them to refund me since the bottles were unopened. The manager insisted that I come back since he had no way to do a "refund". These are bottles paid including MANDATORY gratuity. I would say over $400 per bottle.  Fast Forward.....  Due to pandemic, everything was closed, places were limited. However on the night on November 6, 2020, I decided to pay a visit and ask for the bottles promised. With hope to receive what I paid for, I was DENIED by the owner. According to Manager, owner refused to give me what I PURCHASED. That night, I decided to stay and spend additional money on an establishment that did me wrong.  Customers are always FIRST and the OWNER should be reaching out to me BECAUSE I was refused to RECEIVE what was PAID for by ME. I will reach out to the BANKS and file a CLAIM as messages have been recorded between establishment.  Please UPGRADE your CUSTOMER EXPERIENCE

I usually don't write reviews but I felt compelled to write one about el jefe after what happened to myself and my friend last night. We came here to have a good time but that is definitely not what happened. My friend was called stupid in Spanish by a security guard near the bathroom for doing absolutely nothing. When she replied to him in Spanish (because they assumed that she was not Hispanic because of her skin being dark) the security guard then decided to be nice. After that we stepped outside for a bit and upon entering el jefe my friend was approached by security guards. They then forcefully grabbed her by the arms and told her she needed to leave. She did not do anything to deserve that. As she was escorted I went to close her tab and met with her outside only to find her crying because how she was treated for doing ABSOLUTELY nothing. I went back in to use the restroom and at that point a security guard grabbed my arm and told me that I am not allowed back in. My friend and I were no threat to anyone in el jefe but because of the color of our skin we were mistreated by men at that. One should never feel like because of the color of their skin they would be treated with disrespect. I will never come to this place. I've had different experiences living uptown that were racist because I am African American. If you are African American don't come here because you will get treated like an outcast. Its sad that we are still dealing with this today.
